{"questionId":"9829","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Happy Straw Company manufactures drinking straws.</p>\n<p>The straws are packaged in small closed rectangular boxes, each with length 8 cm, width 4 cm&nbsp;and height 3 cm. The information is shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/2e2c01e0ec88edea5a6fb1b1e3c4e5513ac32546.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Each week, the Happy Straw Company sells <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> boxes of straws. It is known that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{\\text{d}}P}}{{{\\text{d}}x}} =&nbsp; - 2x + 220\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>P</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>d</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>220</mn>\n</math></span>, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> ≥ 0, where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n</math></span> is the weekly profit, in dollars, from the sale of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> thousand boxes.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the number of boxes that should be sold each week to maximize the profit.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" - 2x + 220 = 0\">\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>220</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 110\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>110</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">110 000 (boxes)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9829","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.4c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the number of boxes that should be sold each week to maximize the profit.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.3—Differentiating polynomials, n E Z","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}